Event Description: Indicates that the disconnector has been remotely disconnected.
Indicates that the disconnector has been remotely connected.
Indicates that the disconnector has been locally disconnected (i.e. via the limiter or current suppervision monitors).
Indicates that the a failure of disconnection or reconnection has happened.
Indicates that the disconnector has been locally connected (i.e. via the limiter or current supervision monitors).
Indicates that the terminal cover has been removed.

Indicates that a strong magnetic DC field has been detected.

Indicates a complete power down of the device.Please note that this is related to the device and not necessarily to the network.

Event Description: Indicates that the current on L2 phase is reverse for longer than the time delay was ended.
